From 6bb52ac56e4f73f02860d62d3075d4693e3e7120 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kannan Saravanan <kannsara@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 23 Jul 2025 15:39:58 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] QSDK: Platform: wifi:ath12k Add Base support for WSI
 Bypass feature.

This patch implements support for bypassing the WSI hardware link to
enable power savings in multi-target systems.
This feature allows selective deactivation of interfaces while maintaining
multi-link operation through the WSI ring.

Changes added:

During target bypass,

1. Send MLO teardown for all links, including UMAC reset with the
   appropriate reason code.
2. Issue a PDEV suspend command for the interface to be bypassed.
3. Clean up all resources associated with the bypassed interface.
4. Transition the PCIe interface of the chip into low-speed mode.
5. Send a new QMI message containing updated adjacency information post-bypass.
6. Reinitialize MLO setup and readiness on the remaining active chips.
7. Achieve power savings by sending the PDEV suspend and Mode OFF sequence to
   firmware. The firmware includes a recipe to shut down all Q6 hardware blocks
   except the WSI block, ensuring the WSI ring remains operational for
   multi-link continuity.

During target readdition,

1. Restore the PCIe link to its default speed.
2. Power down and then power up the Q6 subsystem.
3. Allow Q6 to follow the default initialization flow, including QMI setup
   and subsequent sequences.
4. Send updated adjacency information to firmware using the QMI
   MLO reconfiguration message.

Add appropriate checks to ensure the bypassed chip is correctly handled
throughout the process.

Patch-dependency:
	0461-0001-QSDK-Platform-Add-support-for-MLO-reconfig-QMI-messa.patch

Signed-off-by: Kannan Saravanan <kannsara@qti.qualcomm.com>
